sub_title: Assistant Professor at University of Amsterdam
summary: I am an assistant professor at the Institute of Physics at the University of Amsterdam. Before starting my current role, I was a Postdoc, Wellcome Trust Interdisciplinary, and Leverhulme Early Career Fellow at the Department of Applied Mathematics and Theoretical Physics at the University of Cambridge. Before that, I was a postdoc at Physics of Fluids group at Max Planck - University of Twente Center for Complex Fluids. I did a Ph.D. in Complex Fluids Lab at the University of British Columbia.
